content: Red_Zombie, jamphen, tianxia, weigui, Before, mayhem, coco_yuang, scm2000, shuwang, luwenzhe, fallnavy, Xespok, yyfcsd, killer21st, Guest268, virag, sosei, eastmen.
despite all the obstacles, we got our lesson going :)
For the next 4 months, our lesson will be on Tuesdays.
I will later update the info on website.
the new dan system is already working,
and you may apply for your dan title.
within 24 hours of the launch of the new system,
I got already one application for 1 dan.
After reviewing, I will announce his dan,
and likely, he will take the lead position in student list
because now we sort names by dan!
Now, lets continue with study part/
I will present a game from ORC today.
I have many loss games, especially in short games,
but still, many losses are useful for me,
I get some ieas from them.
This time I show you the game where I was white,
is that why scm and I know him? :)
He has joined ORC just as many other masters/
I met him first time 15 years ago.
He does not have big renju titles,
but he is a very stable player,
Maybe he will have new rise in renju career,
now a big threat to me and scm :)
just like Makarov and  Mihailov, A, did.
This was the start of the game, I was white, Filippov was black.
What do black play here usually?
Has anyone seen this 11th move before?
and in short game, there is no time to analyse.
if you were white here, where would you play the next move
while playing, I was thinking of same moves - f11 or j8 or k8
I did not know for sure,
whether I need to attack or defend.
It is not an easy question.
It is active, and helps white to have some counter materials
but take an important field of blacks.
j8 is a defense move, but also a bit active.
I chose j8, just for testing.
Later, turned out, maybe white is not so good.
So, before we go on with the game,
lets take a look at other possibilities.
It may be important for all of you
because your opponent might surprise you with this 11 anytime, right?
you likely have the plan for 14 too
maybe cannot be called as a vct,just dirrect style
sorry,miss the defence of 23, take it too easy
I dont know win or not
I can't see white win, but seems white can get quite comfortable
I guess white may have win chance somewhere,
but maybe not easy to check all in short time
so lets do it at home/
black might just use positional style
Anyway, I had to decide fast,
taking first f11 and than a passive move?
Now I had no choice - I had to keep the aggressive style
because else black has both left side and right side power
and I would be in big trouble.
Black could use threes here now.
but as you see, black cannot easily get the tempo to go to left side (e11) first.
Can anyone of you tell me if black could get the tempo from move 17?
so that black can later go to e11 first?
this is VERY important skill of renju
to find the way to win tempo
in future, when we make more renju puzzles,
i will create such special puzzles
slamduk you need to pay attention
it is so easy to find out who is really "thinking" here
can black win tempo here? yes/no
the idea was to teach the tactical thinking,
we have failed to reach to e11
even there are many possibilities here for black,
we focused shortly on the principal question,
if we have promising base on other side
he realized, he cannot get tempo
so he used a kind of waiting style
at the same time, he was smart and did not waste his threes.
now white could take e11 already.
I wanted to keep up the active struggle,
it was hard to decide about move 22.
weigui, tianxia, killer21st, shuwang, scm2000, SamSite, mayhem, Red_Zombie, fallnavy, yyfcsd, jamphen, coco_yuang, Xespok, Before, slamduk, luwenzhe, Guest268, virag, eastmen, sosei.
in my game, I played here
M4 only place to try be active
23 k6 is more natural and easy?
trying to keep tempo, and keep k10 forbidden
finally he decided now is the moment.
I had just a few seconds
so I just click and click
What's the timing for this game?
but i was in bayomi then
and soon was close to loss
inside stone, but good for defense
and now, white has no win :(
So, a few moves later, I lost the game.
within 1/5 bayomi, it is not easy to find some wins
Black could win with 23-k6, I think.
Here, white should just defend on left with move 18.
No chance for black tempo from move 17.
It seems passive 12th moves are not good,
because black takes valuable f11 point.
Move 12-f11 is best, even if white does not have straight style win.
So, this was a good example of Ando's poor play. :))
you learned today how white can miss good moves 3 times during game
so I just did not learn anything
We end lesson now, wish you all good luck with homework! :)
